    {
      "original": "DSSP/secondary-structure geometry via literature symmetry annotation",
      "substitute": "geometric nearest-neighbor centroid-graph clustering (this script) to auto-detect protofilament membership and layer order directly from coordinates",
      "reason": "The brief does not specify an algorithm for separating protofilaments/ordering layers; cryo-EM deposits do not tag this explicitly in a machine-readable way. A distance-based graph on CA centroids reproduces the known symmetry (verified: 5O3L/5O3T split cleanly into two 5-layer protofilaments at 4.75 A intra-stack vs 9.5 A inter-protofilament, matching the published C2-symmetric PHF architecture).",
